3t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/00 8:58:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> My little cleric alt managed to finally get the undead heart thingy off Grimrot (picked up the Scythe almost 3 weeks ago now), and is all ready to finish the Aegis of Life Quest.<br>
<br>
BUT, I hear that you need a VERY high faction with Qeynos to complete the quest.  Can anyone suggest a good way of bringing up Qeynos faction without hurting other factions?  Preferably a way that doesn't involved killing a billion gnolls or turning in a million sashes either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I hear that there's an NPC (Talar Novashine?) which you can give 2gp to at a time which will increase faction.  Is this true?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any insight you guys can give me!<br>
<br>
Laellanna - Bard of the 49th Tweet<br>
Daena - Cleric of the 30th Bandage<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucamdarlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CamdarLanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/00 2:09:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> hmm,<br>
<br>
Only other one I know of is to turn in the pelts of the rabid grizzleys, it is supposed to give more faction then the sash's anyway.  Should be able to farm quite a few of those with your bard...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Camdar Sol'Dara<br>
Templar of the 57th Heart Lung Machine<br>
&quot;Circle of Truth&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraolf1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raolf1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/00 4:48:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> The sashes are easier to farm, bc its a static spawn of like 10 bandits.  You just need your actual guy there to loot is all.<br>
<br>
Raolf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleanasoulwarden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leana Soulwarden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/00 9:38:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> I went the sash route.  I PL'd newbies.  That way, they got exp and stuff, and I got sashes.<br>
I guess it took about 100 sashes to get my faction.<br>
<br>
Now, with area affect damage, I could do it incredibly quickly.  Walk into a camp, bam, pick up the sashes, move to the next camp.<br>
<br>
BTW, with sashes, you know you have hit the mark when you turn them in and get no Temple of Life faction adjustment.<br>
<br>
Leana Soulwarden<br>
Level 52 Vicar<br>
Inner Fire <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usirarris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Arris</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/arristrueheart/shield.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/00 10:29:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> Hand 2 gp to Lashun Novashine. Went from apprehensive to high warmly in about 250 pp worth.<br>
<br>
Just remember it's 2 Gp, not 2 Pp. <p><hr>
Arris Trueheart<BR>
47th paladin of Mithanniel Marr<BR>
Of the Lanys T'Vyl server
<hr></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uklinddelacroix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klind Delacroix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 3:01:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> The fastest way to raise faction for this quest is simple and you never have to leave Qeynos <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
1st) get a friend to make a level 1 anything... I got a friend to make a monk and gave him throwing stars. Make sure he starts in Qeynos and Bind him By the pond near the ToL.<br>
<br>
2) Have the MonK (or what ever) jump into the water in the pond and kill the level 1 fish... This will get the monk terrible ToL/q faction and will soon be KoS and have to make a new level 1 char... Anyways every 2 to 3 fish will drop a no drop scale. You turn the scales into the pally swimming in the water for massive faction with ToL/Q. in 30 mins I went from indiffrent to LOved by all :P. Just make sure your grouped with the monk so you can loot the scales before they decayed but don't heal/cast a thing while the monk is fighting the fish. You can buff himbefore hand but as long as you don't cast a thing during the fight you won't get a faction hit. even while Grouped <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . The fish can be hard to catch with swimming low is why I gave him trowing starts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Oh and careful <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  if that pally sees you killing a fish he will come on you RIGHT away <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
___________________<br>
Klind Delacroix<br>
53rd Season Vicar and<br>
Proud Officer of Sacred Valor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 6:04:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> All OOC.<br>
<br>
I did this the sash route at the static spawn of a group of bandits in North Karana. Perhaps it was because this is my main (only serious) character, but at the time the money from the selling the numerous bronze weapons was useful too (yes I was in my early 40s levels but since I stopped blacksmithing at about level 25 or so, I've always been poor for my level hehe). It was boring but easy, and sashes dropped thick and fast. Clearing the nearby zombies for zombie skins for pottery between bandit spawns also passed some time, and then the actually killing of putrids during my almost 2-month camp (on and off) of Grimmy himself also gave a big faction adjustment. I'd maxed my temple of life faction long before my guildmate Brizzo downed the undead Grimrot one night while I was not online and helped me finish the quest.<br>
<br>
Grimrot. Sheesh I can't bare to think of the time I wasted sitting by that ring. Bah!<br>
<br>
Felishanna Secretlight<br>
Cleric of Tunare of 55 Seasons,<br>
Mithril Web (www.mithrilweb.com)<br>
Lanys T'Vyl<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 8:28:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> WOW!... thanks for the quick replies everyone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I got a few sashes, but I thought that it was going to be too slow, so I started doing the 2gp to Lashun Novashine thing.  Egads did that take a long time!<br>
<br>
Needless to say 2 hours (well... actually 3, but who's counting the hour that I fell asleep?), I finally had high warmly and converted that Lord Grimrot stuff into an Aegis of Life!<br>
<br>
Ack!... yeah, that would be a HORRIBLE camp, but all I did was leave Laellanna camped there and I logged her in before I logged Daena in to regularly play with.  Doing this over 3 weeks got me lucky enough to run into Lord Grimrot (live) 2 times, and Grimrot (undead) once.  Not too bad I guess.<br>
<br>
Thanks again everyone! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Laellanna - Semi-Retired Bard of the 49th Tweet<br>
Daena - Cleric of the 31st Bandage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaindiacrimsonwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aindia Crimsonwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 12:50:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> Heh I've had the scythe and heart for months *sigh* Just not had the faction...see I was bad lol I killed some silly bards a few times and I'm sure I'm KOS in Qeynos to more then bards.  Thanks tho for asking 'bout this.. it's been something I've wanted to do..but never really got around to doing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><p align=center><b><font size=4><font color=crimson>~Aindia Crimsonwind~</b></font><br><font size=2>51st Cleric of Tunare</font><br><b><font size=2>Member of     <a href=http://geocities.com/thechosenclan target="web">The Chosen Clan</a></font></b></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uranor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 2:08:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> Another question, how ofetn did you check if the Pally would give you the quest.  Last night I decided to get the faction high enough to do the quest, I started WARMLY turned in 140 gold (2 gp at a time), didnt recieve the quest, did another 140 gold, no go, then another 140 and he gave me the quest (and I agree, what a mind numbing experience).  I remember when the quest came out there was talk that even if you were given the quest and turned in the items, you may not get the Shield, but have heard that was fixed, so that was why I am asking.<br>
<br>
Thank you in advance<br>
<br>
Ohh, want to add, you can give Lovishine (mispelled) 4 bone chips at a time (stacked, he asks for 2, but I tried to see what would happen if I gave him more, and he would take the 4 bone chips but no more) to get faction and exp <p>Ranor Lifebringer
Human Cleric
Code of Honor Officer</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uranor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranor</A> at: 9/22/00 2:12:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umerzak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merzak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 3:00:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> Congrats on getting the quest parts.<br>
<br>
I had also read of the pally not giving the Aegis.  On advice I read on other boards, I petitioned a GM to come and witness me completing the quest.  It didn't take too long for the GM to show up.  She made me talk to the pally to get the quest and then I turned in the parts.  He did give the Aegis I'm happy to say.<br>
<br>
Considering how tough it was to get the quest parts I would gladly have waited hours for a GM to show up rather than take the chance of having to do it again.<br>
<br>
Good luck,<br>
<br>
Merzak - The Royal Knights<br>
Cleric of Lanys<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uranor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/22/00 4:50:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> Merzak,<br>
<br>
Good move, and I will try the same thing, I take it you did the quest fairly recently, the post I have read that said they didnt receive the shield was before June (if I remember correctly). <p>Ranor Lifebringer
Human Cleric
Code of Honor Officer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/25/00 11:04:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aegis of Life Quest / Qeynos Faction</span><hr size=1> What I did about checking faction, was the /con Lashun Novashine every 100gp or so.  I noticed that Daena (dwarf cleric) would go up in faction class (dubious -&gt; indifferent -&gt; kindly -&gt; warmly) every 500gp or so.  So I *prayed* (heh, pun  intended!) that once I hit warmly, that I would max out another 500gp later.<br>
<br>
Turns out that was the case.  Never thought about asking a GM to witness, that's a good idea though!<br>
<br>
Laellanna - Bardie of the 49th Tweet<br>
